    "body": "@ytinasni We don't currently have a notion of an illegal path. There are paths that perhaps don't parse the way you expect, but the only way to actually throw an error is if your path contains non-utf8 (on Windows) or NUL. I don't think it's appropriate to make e.g. \"C:a\\b\" throw an error.\n\nGiven that, we need to figure out some way to parse \"C:a\" that makes sense. We could just interpret it as \"C:\\a\", although that strikes me as less than ideal.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
