    "updated_at": "2014-01-21T15:31:54Z",
    "body": "If this is only partially supported by applications written by Microsoft itself, I'd be in favor of undoing this patch. To handle this error, we could add a `std::path::windows::drive_relative_path` condition that gets raised for `\"C:foo\"` paths. Then it's at least clear to the user that we're explicitly disallowing this path and not just silently passing it along like Python `ntpath` library appears to do with:\n\n```\n>>> ntpath.abspath(\"C:foo\")\n'\\\\Users\\\\erickt\\\\C:foo'\n```\n",
